What we have defined here are a form of truncated -returns for TD-learning. These are the only kind that we experiment with, in our paper. We use truncated -returns because the A3C algorithm is designed in a way which makes it suitable for extension under truncated -returns. We leave the problem of generalizing our work to the full -returns as well as eligibility-traces (-returns are the forward view of eligibility traces) to future work.

